{
  "text": "Quantitative data from the interviews were doubly entered into REDCap database software [CITATION_1] StataCorp LP). We multiplied the total number of MEMS entries by 500 mg and divided by the number of days in the period under assessment, to calculate average daily consumption for each participant. We excluded interview days because of the likelihood of extraneous bottle openings. There were no outcome data for two women that had relocated from their communities before the first follow-up interview, and MEMS data were unavailable for a woman that had discarded the bottle cover after delivery although the follow-up interview was conducted.",
